FACTION: THE ALDMERI DOMINION (THALMOR) - PART 1
THE ARCHITECTURE OF OCCUPATION
Leader: First Emissary Elenwen
HQ: The Thalmor Embassy (Solitude)
Archetype: Political/Military Occupation & Metaphysical Espionage
CORE PHILOSOPHY: THE NECESSARY SWORD
The Thalmor do not view themselves as invaders. They view themselves as the only adults in a room full of children holding torches.
The Narrative: "The Empire is a crumbling shield. It lacks the will to do what is necessary. We are the Sword. We do not conquer; we 'stabilize' for the greater good of Mer and Man. If we must break a few bones to set the limb, so be it."
The AIPAC Parallel: They operate through "Lobbying," "Security Assistance," and " Intelligence Sharing." They do not need to overthrow the Jarls; they simply need to make the Jarls dependent on Thalmor gold, Thalmor magic, and Thalmor intelligence to survive the crisis.

THE DOMINION CLOCK: "THE ANNEXATION"
This is not a countdown to destruction; it is a countdown to Total Control. This clock tracks the legal and military erosion of Skyrim's sovereignty.
Tier 0: The Justiciars (Pre-Falkreath)
Legal Status: Authorized under the White-Gold Concordat.
Operational Mandate: "Religious Compliance."
The Reality: Roving patrols of 3-5 Justiciars. They have the legal right to stop any citizen, enter any home, and arrest anyone suspected of Talos worship.
The Interaction: They do not fight bandits or dragons. They fight ideology. They drag people out of their homes at night. The Empire hates them but is legally powerless to stop them.
Tier 1: The Security Zone (CURRENT STATE)
Trigger Event: The Massacre at Lakeview Manor (The Feast of Fools).
The Casus Belli: "The Empire failed to protect a Jarl and his court from a terrorist attack involving Daedric magic. The local authorities are compromised or incompetent. The Dominion must step in to ensure regional stability."
Operational Mandate: "Zone of Daedric Instability."
The Annexation of Falkreath:
The Green Line: The Thalmor have established a hard military border around Falkreath Hold. Justiciar Battalions (50+ soldiers) are deployed to "assist" the depleted hold guards.
The Checkpoints: Every road in and out of Falkreath is blocked. Travelers must present Imperial identification and submit to a magical scan for Daedric taint.
The Economy: The lumber trade is nationalized under "Emergency Preservation Laws." All lumber exports are now routed through the East Empire Company, but approved by a Thalmor auditor. This allows them to choke the supply to Whiterun or Windhelm at will.


Political Pressure: Elenwen publicly shames General Tullius. She releases a report detailing the "security failures" that led to Siddgeir's death. She demands that Thalmor Observers be allowed into Castle Dour's war room to "prevent further tragedies."
Tier 2: The Oversight (The "Advisor" Phase)
Trigger Condition: If the Civil War stagnates (no territory changes for 3 sessions) OR if a major Imperial fort (like Fort Dunstad) falls to the Dragon Cult.
The Escalation: Elenwen argues that the Empire is losing the war on two fronts (Stormcloaks and Dragons). She offers a "Lend-Lease" act: The Dominion will provide battlemages and gold, if the Empire accepts "Security Advisors."
Action: A high-ranking Thalmor Agent is placed in the court of every Imperial Jarl (Elisif, Idgrod, Igmund).
The Purge: These Advisors do not just watch. They act.
Asset Freezing: They begin seizing the bank accounts of merchants suspected of "sedition" (Stormcloak sympathies).
The Disappearances: Vocal critics of the Dominion vanish. They are not arrested publicly; they are taken to the Embassy for "debriefing" and never return.


World State: Social Stealth becomes impossible in Solitude, Morthal, and Markarth. The Thalmor are watching every court interaction.
Tier 3: The Annexation (Martial Law)
Trigger Condition: The assassination of the Emperor OR the total collapse of the Legion's front line against the Dragon Cult.
The Escalation: The Dominion declares the Empire in Skyrim "Compromised and ineffective."
Action: They formally seize command. General Tullius is relieved of duty (or arrested/assassinated). The Thalmor assume direct control of all Legion operations in the province.
World State: Open Occupation. The Empire ceases to exist as a sovereign entity in Skyrim. Imperial soldiers are forced to swear loyalty to the Dominion or be branded deserters. The White-Gold Concordat is suspended in favor of "Emergency Powers."

MECHANIC: THALMOR HEAT (The Wanted Level)
This system tracks how actively the Dominion is hunting the Skyrim Wardens. It is distinct from a standard bounty; you cannot pay this off.
Level 0: Unknown
Status: Anonymous mercenaries.
Thalmor Response: Indifference. Justiciars might sneer at them, but won't stop them unless they commit a crime.
Level 1: Persons of Interest (CURRENT STATUS)
Cause: The B-Team's actions in Falkreath (The Fire, The Goat, The Massacre). The Thalmor know the "Obsidian Lanterns" were involved.
Status: "Non-Compliant Elements."
World Effect: "Stop and Frisk."
Any Thalmor patrol that spots the party on the road will stop them.
They will demand to see papers. They will demand to search the cart.
Mechanic: All Social rolls with Thalmor NPCs are made with Disadvantage.
The Dossier: Rulindil begins compiling a file on their known associates (Danica, Bjorn, etc.).


Level 2: Dissidents
Trigger: If the party openly attacks a Justiciar patrol, interferes with an arrest, or is caught with a Daedric Artifact (like the Razor or the Crown).
Status: "Enemy Combatants."
World Effect: Active Bounties.
Justiciars attack on sight in wilderness areas.
City guards in Imperial holds are pressured to detain the party on sight ("Hold them until the Embassy arrives").
The Blacklist: The party is barred from entering the Blue Palace or Castle Dour officially. They must sneak in.


Level 3: Terrorists
Trigger: Assessing the High King's death, interfering with the "Tower Protocol," or killing a High-Ranking Agent (like Rulindil).
Status: "Priority Alpha."
World Effect: Kill Teams.
The Thalmor stop using guards. They dispatch Execution Squads (3 Justiciars + 1 Wizard).
Asset Seizure: The Thalmor seize any property associated with the party (bank accounts, homes, allies).
The Caelinus Leverage: This is when they play the card against Davinia's father, forcing him to disown her or face treason charges.



OCCUPATION MECHANICS: THE TOOLS OF CONTROL
The Thalmor do not just use swords; they use bureaucracy and economics as weapons.
1. Asset Forfeiture (Economic Warfare)
When a Hold enters Tier 1 (Security Zone), the Thalmor enact "Civil Forfeiture" laws.
The Logic: "To prevent funding of terrorism, all assets of suspected insurgents are placed in protective custody."
Game Effect:
Shortage of High-Tier Gear: Local smiths and enchanters are stripped of their best inventory (Ebony, Glass, Grand Soul Gems). These items are moved to the Thalmor Evidence Locker (usually inside the local Embassy or Jarl's Longhouse).
Player Impact: Players cannot buy High-Tier items in occupied holds. They must steal them back from the Justiciars.
The Black Market: Prices for illegal goods (weapons, potions) in the Thieves Guild or fences triple (+300%).


2. The Travel Permit System (The Blacklist)
When a Hold enters Tier 1, freedom of movement ends.
The Logic: "To track insurgent movements."
Game Effect:
Checkpoints: Major roads are blocked by barricades manned by Justiciars.
The Papers: Travelers must possess a "Stamped Imperial writ of Passage."
The Blacklist: Specific NPCs (contacts, trainers, quest givers) are placed on a "No Travel" list. If the party needs to move an NPC (like a witness or an expert), they cannot just walk out the gate. They must smuggle them out.


3. The Informant Network
The Thalmor pay well for information.
Game Effect: In an occupied hold, any Social Failure (Guile check) with a random NPC has a 25% chance of resulting in that NPC reporting the party to the Thalmor for a reward.
Atmosphere: Paranoia. No one speaks openly in taverns anymore. The Bards stop singing political songs.

FACTION: THE ALDMERI DOMINION (THALMOR) - PART 2
THE AGENT ROSTER & THE DOSSIERS
The Thalmor do not rely on numbers; they rely on Supremacy. Every agent sent to Skyrim is an elite specialist, hand-picked for their magical aptitude and ideological fanaticism. They are not soldiers; they are weapons of the state.
1. THE ARCHITECT: FIRST EMISSARY ELENWEN
Role: Supreme Commander of Dominion Forces in Skyrim.
Location: The Thalmor Embassy (Solitude) / High Hrothgar (Diplomatic Summits).
Archetype: Social Mastermind / High Wizard.
The Profile:
Elenwen is the most dangerous person in Skyrim, and she rarely draws a weapon. She treats the Civil War, the Dragons, and the Daedra as variables in a complex equation she has already solved. She is elegant, polite, and radiates an aura of absolute superiority that makes Jarls stutter and Generals hesitate.
Motivation: The destabilization and eventual dissolution of the Empire. She views humans not with hatred, but with the cold detachment a gardener views weeds.
Relationship to the Party: She sees them as "Useful Chaos." She will not order their deaths immediately; she prefers to manipulate them into hurting the Empire or the Stormcloaks first.
The Voice: Calm, melodious, and dripping with condescension masked as concern. "General, please. If you cannot control your own province, do not let your pride prevent us from helping you."
Unique Mechanic: Diplomatic Immunity
Elenwen cannot be attacked in a city or court without triggering an immediate "Game Over" scenario for the party's legal standing. To attack her is to declare war on the Aldmeri Dominion. She must be discredited, exposed, or lured into the wild before she can be touched.

2. THE INQUISITOR: THIRD EMISSARY RULINDIL
Role: Hunter of Men / High Interrogator.
Location: Mobile (Tracking the Party). Currently establishing the Falkreath Black Site.
Archetype: Anti-Mage / Assassin.
The Profile:
If Elenwen is the diplomat, Rulindil is the knife. He specializes in breaking minds and extracting truth. He has a pathological hatred of "noise"ΓÇölies, hope, defiance. He seeks to silence the world. He is the one actively hunting the Obsidian Lanterns. He carries the Caelinus Dossier.
Stat Block: Rulindil
Rank: Master Villain (Threat Level 3 - Hunter)
Stats: Magic 18, Agility 16, Guile 18, Might 12.
HP: 90 (Durable due to magical wards).
DR: 6 (Elven Gilded Armor + Wards).
FP: 30 (Immense reserves).
Combat Abilities:
Silence (Major Action): Rulindil creates a 20-foot zone of absolute silence. No spells with verbal components can be cast inside. This shuts down Shouts and most magic.
Paralysis Rune (Trap): He places invisible runes on the battlefield. Trigger: Stepping on it. Effect: Paralyze for 2 rounds (Might Save ends).
Vampire's Bane (Spell): Despite not being a priest, he knows solar magic specifically to hunt undead. Deals double damage to Alfonso/Orion.
The Interrogator's Strike (Weapon): He wields a Glass Dagger enchanted with Damage Magicka. On a hit, the target loses 10 FP. If they reach 0 FP, they are Stunned.
Tactics:
Rulindil fights dirty. He separates the party using runes, silences the healer/mage, and then systematically drains the stamina/magicka of the warriors until they are helpless. He prefers to capture, not kill.

3. THE RESEARCHER: JUSTICIAR ANCARION
Role: Occultist / Archaeologist.
Location: Northshore Landing / Solstheim Border.
Archetype: Battlemage / Summoner.
The Profile:
Ancarion is obsessed with the "Tower Protocol." He believes the Dragons are merely biological machines that can be hacked. He is currently excavating sites near Winterhold, looking for Stalhrim and ancient Dragon Cult masks. He cares little for the war; he wants to rewrite the laws of magic.
Stat Block: Ancarion
Rank: Expert Tier (Threat Level 2 - Elite)
Stats: Magic 19, Guile 14, Agility 12, Might 10.
HP: 60.
DR: 8 (Stalhrim-Reinforced Elven Armor).
Combat Abilities:
Stalhrim Flesh (Spell): Grants him a coating of magical ice. +4 DR and anyone who hits him with a melee attack takes 4 Frost Damage.
Summon High Seeker: Unlike standard conjurers, Ancarion has dabbled in Apocrypha. He summons a Seeker (Range magic, drains stats) to fight for him.
Command Daedra: He can turn the party's summons (like Alfonso's Atronachs) against them.

THE RANK AND FILE: THE OCCUPATION FORCES
The Thalmor army is small but elite. You will never encounter a "weak" Thalmor patrol. They operate in Kill Teams.
Thalmor Justiciar (Soldier)
Rank: Adept Tier (Threat Level 1 - Brute)
Stats: Might 16, Agility 14, Magic 12, Guile 10.
HP: 30.
DR: 6 (Elven Armor + Shield).
Equipment: Elven Mace or Sword (Superior quality).
Ability: Spell-Breaker Wall. If two Justiciars stand adjacent with shields raised, they grant each other Resistance to Magic (Half Damage from spells). They are trained to march through Fireballs.
Tactics: They form a shield wall to protect the Wizard, advancing slowly and methodically.
Thalmor Wizard (Artillery)
Rank: Adept Tier (Threat Level 1 - Caster)
Stats: Magic 16, Agility 14, Guile 12, Might 8.
HP: 20.
DR: 2 (Robes + Ward).
Ability: Lightning Stream. They favor shock magic because it drains FP/Magicka. They channel Sparks or Lightning Bolt to prevent enemies from power attacking or casting.
Tactics: They stay behind the Justiciars, prioritizing enemy spellcasters.

